# Copy to .env.local (which is gitignored) and fill in from your Supabase project:
#   Supabase dashboard -> Project Settings -> API
#
# Both of these are PUBLIC values. The anon key is designed to ship in client
# JavaScript; every real access rule lives in the row-level security policies in
# supabase/migrations/. That is why the schema matters more than the key does.
#
# NEVER put the service_role key in this file, in the repo, or in any client build.
# It bypasses row-level security entirely.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
